value.0: Oh, really. Very interesting. You can find a druid locked in the southwest most room. Don't worry, she has not been harmed. I'm too lazy to find my key, so do whatever you need to do to open her cell.
I have in my possession an enchanted amulet that can prolong your life, as well as make your vigorous and healthy. Does that not pique your curiosity?

The only thing that holds true value for me is my beauty. There are sirines who lives in this forest that have magical mirrors that can return my beauty. I overheard two dryads talking about it, just before all this trouble started.

They live to the northeast of here. I would get it myself, but I can't go anywhere near them. The unearthly beauty of their faces physically hurts me, and they shun me because I am ugly. Please, please get me the mirror!
I will give you an enchanted amulet that can prolong your life... if that is indeed the reward you desire. Ha! But only when we make the trade, not before.

Oh thank you! You dear <man/woman>. I look forward to the return of the dazzling beauty I once possessed. Should you be successful, I will gladly give you an enchanted amulet that can prolong your life.
That greedy elf sent you here? Did he tell you to kill me and take steal my gem? I think you underestimate my power.
I certainly don't think that you improved your chances by busting in here and killing all my servants. Not exactly tactful, is it?
But, I might have a use for you, since you are so interested in... acquiring objects for others. We might be able to make a deal.
I see you are back. What do you want?
Bah! I have far more important manners than going around, talking to each of my servant to make an exception for you. Besides, I am sure you are still helping yourself to my posessions.
Steal anything in these rooms, however, and I turn you to dust faster than you can say fireball.
Oh, yes, yes, YES! I am so glad I trusted you with the task. Now I can be cured. You will be blessed to look upon my true, dazzling beauty.

value.0: I know you didn't help me out of the kindness in your heart, so here is your amulet. Perhaps if you wear it, it can make you live as long as I have.
Now, look at me! It worked. I'm beautiful again! I'll bet that you never expected me to be so incredibly stunning now did you?
Oh, it's true, it's true! Oh, I am so very beautiful. Good luck adventurers!
They live somewhere to the northwest of here. If you find arrogant young tarts in simple clothing, surrounded by a small army of incoherent slaves, then you've found them.
I will give you the gem once you bring me the sirine's mirror. Until then, no deal! Now begone.
Seeing as you have recovered the mirror for me, I suppose I can let you have the gem. It is of no use to me. Now, leave me.
I was sent here to collect a gem you have.
No, I was just hoping to convince you to let me have it.
Can you call off your servants? I'm tired of getting attacked in here.
About Elaith's gem...
Where did you say the sirines are again?
I am here to collect Elaith's gem.
